validate-spec.sh - Spec Folder Validation Orchestrator (v2.0)

USAGE: ./validate-spec.sh <folder-path> [OPTIONS]

OPTIONS:
    --help, -h     Show help     --version, -v  Show version
    --json         JSON output   --strict       Warnings as errors
    --verbose      Detailed      --quiet, -q    Results only
    --recursive    Validate parent + all [0-9][0-9][0-9]-*/ child phase folders
    --no-recursive Disable auto-recursive validation when phase children exist

EXIT CODES: 0=pass, 1=user error, 2=validation error, 3=system error

RULES BY CATEGORY:
  authored_template:
    FILE_EXISTS [error] - Validates required spec documents for the declared documentation level.
    PLACEHOLDER_FILLED [error] - Rejects unfilled template placeholders in authored spec documents.
    SECTIONS_PRESENT [warn] - Checks that required high-level markdown sections are present.
    LEVEL_DECLARED [info] - Reports whether the documentation level was declared or inferred.
    PRIORITY_TAGS [warn] - Validates P0/P1/P2 priority tags on checklist items.
    EVIDENCE_CITED [warn] - Checks completed checklist/tasks items for evidence citations.
    ANCHORS_VALID [error] - Validates anchor syntax, pairing, order, and uniqueness.
    FRONTMATTER_MEMORY_BLOCK [error] - Validates canonical _memory continuity frontmatter blocks.
    SPEC_DOC_SUFFICIENCY [error] - Checks implementation-summary sufficiency after save/write flows.
    TOC_POLICY [error] - Enforces table-of-contents placement policy.
    PHASE_LINKS [warn] - Checks parent/child phase-link consistency.
    PHASE_PARENT_CONTENT [warn] - Warns when phase-parent spec.md includes migration-history narrative tokens.
    AI_PROTOCOLS [error] - Validates AI execution protocol sections in high-governance specs.
    COMPLEXITY_MATCH [error] - Checks declared level against content complexity signals.
    FOLDER_NAMING [error] - Validates numbered spec-folder naming conventions.
    FRONTMATTER_VALID [error] - Validates YAML frontmatter structure and required semantic values.
    LEVEL_MATCH [error] - Checks required files match the declared documentation level.
    SECTION_COUNTS [error] - Checks section-count expectations for authored spec documents.
    SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY [error] - Verifies inline markdown references resolve within spec docs.
    TEMPLATE_SOURCE [error] - Checks SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE provenance markers.
    TEMPLATE_HEADERS [error] - Checks required template header order and naming.
  operational_runtime:
    MERGE_LEGALITY [error] - Validates generated merge payloads against target anchor shape.
    CROSS_ANCHOR_CONTAMINATION [error] - Detects route/category mismatches before generated content is merged.
    POST_SAVE_FINGERPRINT [error] - Verifies post-save fingerprints for generated writes.
    GRAPH_METADATA_PRESENT [warn] - Checks generated description and graph metadata are present.
    NORMALIZER_LINT [error] - Strict-only lint for duplicated runtime normalizer helpers.
    LINKS_VALID [warn] - Validates cross-skill wikilinks when explicitly enabled.
    CANONICAL_SAVE_ROOT_SPEC_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical saves include a root spec reference.
    CANONICAL_SAVE_SOURCE_DOCS_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical saves include source document references.
    CANONICAL_SAVE_LINEAGE_REQUIRED [error] - Ensures canonical save lineage metadata is present.
    CANONICAL_SAVE_PACKET_IDENTITY_NORMALIZED [error] - Checks canonical save packet identity normalization.
    CANONICAL_SAVE_DESCRIPTION_GRAPH_FRESHNESS [error] - Checks generated description/graph freshness for canonical saves.
    CONTINUITY_FRESHNESS [warn strict-only] - Strict-mode freshness check for continuity frontmatter.
    EVIDENCE_MARKER_LINT [warn strict-only] - Strict-mode lint for evidence marker formatting.

LEVELS: 1=spec+plan+tasks+impl-summary*, 2=+checklist, 3=+decision-record
        *impl-summary required after tasks completed

